              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1291915-lauren?shelf=india-indian-lit">india-indian-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1906043316" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5557953669960665824">The message of this incredible book distills to a simple phrase: <i>Money changes everything</i>. <br/><br/>The book begins with a near-perfect description of the unnamed main character&apos;s ritual of going to his cafe/sanctuary, and meeting with his barista/guru. I read this section three times as I loved it that much. The story opens up and becomes a parable (of sorts), detailing a family&apos;s rise from poverty to wealth. We see how each character changes - in looks, personality, personal tastes - in a very short am</span>
  <span id="freeText5557953669960665824" style="display:none">The message of this incredible book distills to a simple phrase: <i>Money changes everything</i>. <br /><br />The book begins with a near-perfect description of the unnamed main character's ritual of going to his cafe/sanctuary, and meeting with his barista/guru. I read this section three times as I loved it that much. The story opens up and becomes a parable (of sorts), detailing a family's rise from poverty to wealth. We see how each character changes - in looks, personality, personal tastes - in a very short amount of time. <br /><br />A stunning story, and one that I will recommend to others - as a short and accessible piece, it really packs the punch. Loved it.<br /><br />Longer spoken review and discussion of this book on <a href="http://readingenvy.blogspot.com/2017/10/reading-envy-097-blank-spaces-with.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Jenny's Reading Envy Podcast 097: Blank Spaces</a> (guest: me!)</span>
  <a data-text-id="5557953669960665824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
